 Signed<br>
  Rich MOFOS of Verant, Sony Online.<br>
<br>
1. Bind Death Loops<br>
   1.1. Any losses due to bind death loop situations will not be reimbursed, including, but not limited to, corpses, items, and experience, regardless of the magnitude of the loss. <br>
      1.1.1 Note: Please remember to only be bound in safe places. <br>
<br>
2. Characters Level 1-5<br>
   2.1. Characters of these levels will not receive reimbursement of any kind relating to items/coins or experience.<br>
      2.1.1 Note: We strongly advise against giving important items to characters below level 6.<br>
<br>
3. Coins<br>
   3.1. Coins (platinum, gold, silver, and copper) will not be reimbursed, regardless of the circumstance.<br>
<br>
4. Combined Items<br>
   4.1. Items lost when combined in mobile containers, such as sewing kits, toolboxes, bags, etc. or world containers, such as forges, ovens, etc. (intentionally or accidentally) will not be reimbursed.<br>
<br>
5. Deleted/Missing Player Characters<br>
   5.1. Deleted/Missing characters may be restored, but those that were deleted may not be restored with their equipment.<br>
   5.2. Deleted/Missing characters will not be restored with equipment that has been traded, dropped, destroyed, or otherwise legitimately lost.<br>
         5.2.1. Note: A restore of a deleted or missing character cannot be guaranteed, including any items of any kind that were on the character at the time of deletion. It is imperative you contact the server GM immediately if you wish to request a character restore.<br>
<br>
6. Destroyed Items<br>
   6.1. Items that are destroyed, intentionally or accidentally, will not be reimbursed.<br>
      6.1.1 Note: To avoid accidentally destroying an item, we suggest you turn off the fast item destroy option.<br>
<br>
7. Dropped Items<br>
   7.1. Items dropped, intentionally or accidentally, will not be reimbursed.<br>
   7.2. Items that fall to the ground during trades due to a full inventory, or due to those items not fitting into a container will not be reimbursed.<br>
   7.3. Any items that are thrown as a projectile, such as items placed in your range slot, intentionally or accidentally, will not be reimbursed.<br>
      7.3.1 Note: To avoid accidentally dropping an item, we suggest you set the item dropping option to never.<br>
<br>
8. Experience<br>
   8.1. Experience will not be restored for any death caused by latency (a.k.a. &quot;lag&quot;), Link-Death, or other forms of disconnection.<br>
   8.2. Experience will not be restored for any unverifiable bug.<br>
   8.3. Experience will not be restored for any death caused by duels, Player vs. Player combat, or NPC attacks.<br>
   8.4. Experience will not be restored for any loss due to a reset to a previous save.<br>
<br>
9. Faction<br>
   9.1. Any reported abnormality of faction will not be altered by a GM.*<br>
      9.1.1. *Note: There are currently no verifiable bugs that are related to faction. <br>
<br>
10. NO RENT Items and Containers<br>
   10.1. Any item classified as NO RENT and all contents lost in NO RENT containers will not be reimbursed. This includes summoned items.<br>
<br>
11. NPC's/Corpses of NPC's<br>
   11.1. Any disappearing NPC's, items or corpses of an NPC, will not be respawned or reimbursed.<br>
   11.2. Any NO DROP items looted from NPC's will not be transferred or reimbursed, regardless if the looting was intentional* or accidental.<br>
      11.2.1. *Note: Intentional Ninja-Looting will be dealt with as a separate issue. This only applies to situations of non-malicious looting.<br>
<br>
12. PC Corpse Decay<br>
   12.1. Any corpse lost to normal decay rate, including any items on that corpse, will not be reimbursed.<br>
<br>
13. Quests<br>
   13.1. Items lost in any Quest will not be reimbursed, regardless of the circumstance.<br>
   13.2. Items that are lost/reward given to wrong person due to Multi-Questing will not be transferred or reimbursed.<br>
   13.3. NPC's in Quests that disappear or are killed will not be respawned, nor will items on the NPC's be reimbursed.<br>
   13.4. Items lost in any Quest performed incorrectly will not be reimbursed.<br>
<br>
14. Trades<br>
   14.1. Items traded to or sold to other players, pets or other NPC's, intentionally or accidentally, will not be reimbursed.<br>
      14.1.1. Note: GM's will not assist with any trade disputes. All trades are considered final.<br>
<br>
15. Roll-backs<br>
   15.1. Any lost items, experience, or faction due to a reset to a previous save will not be reimbursed.<br>
<br>
Should any unforeseen technical issue occur resulting in the loss of items to our player base as a whole, Customer Service will address these issues separately across all servers.<br>
<br>
If your situation is not addressed in this policy, please use the /petition command for additional assistance. Reimbursements of any kind, regardless of the circumstance, are not guaranteed.<br>
<br>
Reimbursement issues can only be addressed by GM's (SOE/Verant employees), as they have sole responsibility for enforcing this policy. <br>
<br>
If you believe a GM (SOE/Verant employee) is not adhering to this policy, please contact George Scotto, Director of Customer Service at gscotto@station.sony.com or Michelle Butler, EQ Customer Service Manager at mbutler@station.sony.com. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
If you are still having problems after visiting this support section, you can contact our Technical Support Department through an email via our online form.<br>
